				<slide id="business-model-internal">
					<title>The 900lb Gorilla</title>
					<img href="https://www.programmableweb.com/news/programmablewebs-guide-to-modern-api-business-models/analysis/2020/10/26" src="api-business-models-internal.png" class="fullsize"/>
				</slide>
				<slide id="indirect">
					<title>Most API Value Creation is Indirect</title>
					<ol>
						<li>Using APIs to become better at internal reuse and cross-pollination</li>
						<li>Reducing friction by having teams communicate via APIs</li>
						<li>Using <q>API First</q> as a way to build everything as digital building blocks</li>
					</ol>
				</slide>
			</part>
			<part id="platforms">
				<title>Myth #3: API Platforms</title>
				<slide id="platform-types">
					<title>What is a Platform?</title>
					<ol>
						<li>A <em>developer platform</em> that provides support for <em>developing applications</em></li>
						<li>An <em>API platform</em> for discovering digital building blocks</li>
						<li>A <em href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MO1gvOdR84s">platform business</em> as a specific way to design &amp; scale a business model</li>
					</ol>
				</slide>
				<slide id="platformize">
					<title>But we're not Uberâ€¦</title>
					<ul>
